// @check
// @error argument 1: expected an array, got i32
// An un-annotated parameter the body calls an ARRAY METHOD on (`self.map(...)`) is inferred to
// demand an array — the method analogue of indexing (`self[0]`) demanding one. A scalar
// argument therefore can't satisfy it and is rejected at CHECK time (rather than type-checking
// against a `{map: any}` shape it can never match, or failing later at emit). `dbl([1,2,3])` is
// fine; `dbl(5)` is not.

function dbl(self) {
  return self.map((x) => x * 2)
}

print(dbl(5)[0])
